page.title: 06 Weybourne Fete
page.content: The 1985 Weybourne Fete was held at Weybourne recreation ground on 8.6 85. It was a great success. The fete was opened at 1.30 p.m. Following this there was a{ballet {display}and a display of{Ju Jitsu. At 3 p.m, the five mile fun run began. Soon after this there was a {gymnastic display}by the pupils of {William Cobbett Middle School. Next on the agenda were children's races and a tug of war competition.The fun run was won by Mr.S.Bone. Also at the fete there were many stalls,including,tombola,break the china,fish the bottle,bric-a-brac,spin the wheel and refreshments.As well as the stalls previously mentioned,there were pony and cart rides and a car boot sale.
